# Pretty URLs — Netlify-style rewrites the IPFS gateway applies for DNSLink /
# subdomain hosts (enclave.host serves via DNSLink; docs: specs.ipfs.tech/http-
# gateways/web-redirects-file). Rules are evaluated ONLY for paths that do not
# exist in the DAG, so the shipped .html files keep serving at their old URLs
# (the router's history.replaceState canonicalizes those in the address bar).
# Ships from the site root via build-site.mjs; nan-deploy.sh pins it with -r.
/apps       /apps.html       200
/develop    /develop.html    200
/dashboard  /dashboard.html  200
/buy        /buy.html        200
/admin      /admin.html      200
# /deploy and /publish are VIEWS of the Apps page (router aliases): a hard
# load serves the apps document and apps.js picks the view from the pathname.
# (deploy.html stays only as the legacy /deploy.html redirect stub.)
/deploy     /apps.html       200
/publish    /apps.html       200
